    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 857.857/87</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Havre</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Osborne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Sjöstad</hi>, gross 1,755, Newport, Wales, to
                    Fécamp with coal, sunk 28th, noon, locality four or five minutes from Cape
                    Antifer, this district, either torpedoed or mined; 17 in crew; 9 missing and
                    believed drowned, comprising 4 Norwegians, 2 Swedes, 1 Finn, 1 Spaniard, 1
                    American named <persName>Smith</persName>, said to be from New York, aged about
                    25, shipped as fireman, Newport, February 23. Ship’s papers lost. Eight
                    survivors fell in sea; rescued by French torpedo boats, which had convoyed <hi
                        rend="italic">Sjostad</hi>, and brought to Havre. Can not take depositions
                    until 2d.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
